# Equality Analysis (Excel)

## 📌 Overview

In this project, I worked with employee compensation data to understand how fair the distribution is across different factories and job roles. The main idea was to take raw scores and turn them into something easier to read and interpret.

## 🎯 What I Did

* Went through the dataset to understand how the data is structured
* Added a new column called **“Equality Class”** to group the scores
* Used Excel functions (**IFS, AND, OR**) to classify each value into:

  * Fair
  * Unfair
  * Highly Discriminative
* Converted raw numerical values into clear and meaningful categories

## 🛠 Tools Used

* Microsoft Excel (IFS, AND, OR, basic data analysis)

## 📊 Key Insights

* Spotted where compensation is fairly distributed
* Identified cases where inequality is higher and may need attention
* Made the data much easier to understand at a glance

